00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:26,640
where our Habitus is so heavily corporatized,

250
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:29,200
with corporate values being held in such a high regard

251
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:32,160
that we value our careers more than our families.

252
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:34,000
Never before in history has this happened.

253
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,400
Truman's suspicions of reality are then brought up again

254
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:38,640
when his father, who he assumes is dead,

255
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:41,120
shows up on his way to work dressed as a beggar.

256
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:41,680
Dead?

