262
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:53,280
by suggesting that he's just crazy and hallucinated it.

263
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:54,880
This time, it doesn't convince Truman,

264
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:57,920
who also notices how often his wife name drops brands.

265
00:08:57,920 --> 00:08:59,680
As Truman starts to go through his old things,

266
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:01,840
the movie flashes back to Truman's collages

267
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:04,160
and a chance encounter he had with a woman named Lauren.

268
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:06,000
Lauren's meant to be a background character,

269
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,680
but the two sides meet across the room.

270
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:10,240
They share a conversation in a romantic moment on the beach.

271
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,920
Lauren then goes out of character

272
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:14,800
to try to reveal to Truman that his whole reality is fake.

273
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:24,080
Lauren, who reveals her real name as Sylvia,

274
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:26,080
tries to explain that Truman's world is a lie,

275
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:29,520
but then again, she stops short by a man saying he is her father

276
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:31,280
and that she's just talking nonsense.

277
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:33,120
As Truman starts to think back to this,

278
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:35,280
it's revealed that he still longs to see Sylvia,

279
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:38,080
with him even recreating her face from fashion magazines,

280
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:41,040
because Sylvia is the only thing that's real in this fake world.

281
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:43,520
It's then later revealed that Truman is obsessed with Fiji

282
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:45,520
as Sylvia is reported to be moving there.

283
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:48,000
Truman then starts to see more and more suspicious things.

284
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,640
His radio specifically describes his every move

285
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:51,920
in an apparent malfunction.

286
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:58,480
Truman's also seeing every part of the background set,

287
00:09:58,480 --> 00:10:00,320
but he's always escorted away from it.

288
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:03,120
This sequence of events brings his suspicions to a breaking point,

289
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:05,680
as Truman concludes that it seems that his entire world

290
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:07,920
revolves around him in some weird way.

291
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:09,200
Fearing that he's going crazy,

292
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:11,600
he brings up these questions to Marlon, his best friend,

293
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,360
who then just tries to brush it all off.

294
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:15,200
And in response to his increased suspicion,

295
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,200
Truman's then further barraged by suggestions

296
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,680
that everything is just fine, that he's just being weird.

297
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:22,160
His mother then shows fake pictures of him at Mount Rushmore,

298
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:25,920
and even the TV runs a program about the benefits of a small town life.

299
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:28,080
But by now, things don't work like they used to.

300
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,480
He's seen the society that he lives in starts to crack.

301
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:32,400
It's also laughable and ridiculous.

302
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:33,920
This whole thing is a facade.

303
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:36,000
And now that Truman is waking up to this reality,

304
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:38,800
the lullabies of deception can't draw him back to sleep.

305
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:42,000
After noticing that his wife is crossing her fingers in his wedding pictures,

306
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,280
Truman follows her to work.

307
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:46,240
Despite multiple attempts by extras to delay and stop Truman

308
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:48,320
from seeing the surgery that his wife is helping with,

309
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:50,960
Truman breaks into the hospital and sees the fake surgery

310
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:53,760
being played out by actors who have no idea what they're doing.

311
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:56,480
Determined to leave, Truman then visits a travel agency.

312
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:58,000
By this point, Truman's had enough.

313
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,120
He's determined to leave.

314
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,880
He wants to escape this sick society.

315
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:02,640
So he tries to book a flight to Fiji,

316
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:04,960
but the clerk says they're all sold out for at least a month.

317
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:06,560
So then Truman tries to get a bus out,

318
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:08,720
but it conveniently breaks down just before leaving.

319
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,640
Truman then sitting in a car at home,

320
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:12,480
waits for his wife to come back from work.

321
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:14,560
When she does, she gets in the car with him

322
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:16,560
as he points out the clockwork regularity

323
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:18,400
of the people who go past their road.

324
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:20,800
Unsatisfied with her unrealistic reaction to this,

325
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:24,000
Truman then locks the car and takes Meryl on an impromptu road trip.

326
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,160
To everyone around him, he seems like he's having a breakdown.

327
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:28,240
He's breaking the rotten habit of surrounding him.

328
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:31,760
But then instantly traffic jam starts stopping Truman in his tracks.

329
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:33,200
Truman then pretends to go back home,

330
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,720
which disperses the traffic completely.

331
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:36,000
But then turns right around

332
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,320
and makes his way out of the suburbs and onto the road.

333
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:39,280
Once they reach the bridge,

334
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:40,960
which stands between Truman and the mainland,

335
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:44,000
it seems that his conditioned aquaphobia will stop his escape plan.

336
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:47,200
All the conditioning and propaganda is the only barrier to his freedom.

337
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,120
However, Truman overcomes his fears

338
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:51,440
by closing his eyes and forcing Meryl to steer the car

339
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:53,040
while he holds down the accelerator.

340
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:54,240
Once they're over the bridge,

341
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:56,000
other obstacles are set up by Christoff

342
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,440
to try and stop Truman from leaving.

343
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:59,280
Truman even drives through wildfire,

344
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:01,840
but is stopped by a roadblock due to a convenient leak

345
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:03,280
at the nearby power plant.

346
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:05,600
In desperation, Truman tries to get through on foot,

347
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:08,080
but is tackled and subdued by men in hazmat suits,

348
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,200
who take him back home.

349
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:11,200
The implausibility of all these events

350
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:13,440
cement Truman's skepticism of the world around him,

351
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:14,640
which brings up the question,

352
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:17,280
how many so-called emergency events in our own world

353
00:12:17,280 --> 00:12:18,880
could be equally implausible?

354
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:21,200
All the lies told by our media,

355
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:23,200
all the false narratives pushed onto us,

356
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:25,840
all the divisions sowed by algorithms in the news,

357
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:28,400
all these layers of fallacy that have been embedded

358
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:30,400
into every aspect of society.

359
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:32,640
We all have the means to stop this nonsensical

360
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:34,400
fictional reality that we abide by,

361
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:36,320
and yet we choose not to confront it.

362
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,360
When anyone does,

363
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:39,280
they are breaking the habit of surrounding them,

364
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:40,960
which threatens the whole house of cars

365
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:42,320
the society is built on,

366
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:44,400
which is why true authentic reality

367
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:46,320
is always outrunning our apprehension.

368
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:48,000
So then how can we ever know the truth

369
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,120
when the lens we look through

370
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:51,200
is tainted by a corrupted habitus,

371
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,200
tainted by all the models and distractions

372
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:54,640
that we don't even acknowledge?

373
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:56,480
If we can't comprehend true reality,

374
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:58,480
we no longer know what truth is.

375
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:01,040
We don't have a grasp on what our values really are,

376
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:03,040
and it's this flattening of our values,

377
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:04,640
of our society, of our culture

378
00:13:04,640 --> 00:13:06,640
that dampens our outrage and emotion.

379
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:09,360
Everything becomes muted by a post-modern reality.

380
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:10,240
In the Truman Show,

381
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:11,680
Truman's deserved outrage

382
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:13,280
at the cage he has been trapped in

383
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,480
is never tapped into.

384
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:15,520
He's never angry,

385
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:17,600
instead he's always left in a state of confusion

386
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:18,400
and distraction.

387
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:20,960
He's meant to feel crazy by searching for the truth.

388
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:22,960
This is because for the show to be successful,

389
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:24,800
it relies on Truman and his belief

390
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:26,080
in the society around him.

391
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,280
If he starts questioning this,

392
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:28,960
since society goes down with him,

393
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:31,040
so society has to prevent him from questioning

394
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,480
the habitus he is surrounded by.

395
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:33,840
And aren't we any different?

396
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:36,320
Is this why we live in a culture without soul or value?

397
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:37,600
Where everything we think and do

398
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:39,200
is shrink down by reductionism.

399
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,520
Where the phenomena of nature, personality,

400
00:13:41,520 --> 00:13:42,640
the essence of life,

401
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:45,360
is just reduced to statistics and banal labels.

402
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:47,280
Our world is filled with mystery and wonder.

403
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:48,400
It's filled with adventure,

404
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:49,760
but our world is being reduced

405
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:52,320
to nothing more than a banal monotonous cage,

406
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:55,520
numbing us into this bored, flaccid, apathetic state,

407
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:57,520
which is what the Truman Show tries to show us.

408
00:13:57,600 --> 00:14:00,240
Once home, Truman is now feeling like an animal in a cage.

409
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:02,080
His wife, unable to come down,

410
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:03,120
offers him some coffee

411
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:04,960
with a less than subtle product placement.

412
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,480
Truman immediately senses out the fact

413
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:07,920
that she is performing for someone,

414
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:09,520
and so he confronts her about it.

415
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:11,520
He's starting to reject this ridiculous reality

416
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:12,560
he is surrounded by,

417
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,320
and because of this, he seems crazy,

418
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:16,480
which is why then the actor of Truman's wife

419
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,680
begins to break character

420
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:20,080
and pulls out a sharpened kitchen utensil

421
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:21,280
to defend herself.

422
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:22,640
It's these sorts of cracks in the show

423
00:14:22,640 --> 00:14:25,280
that only happen when Truman stops believing in it.

424
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:25,920
Like in our world,

425
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:28,320
we're now starting to see the rise of political outsiders.

426
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:29,760
We're seeing the rise of extremism

427
00:14:29,760 --> 00:14:31,520
and a general apathy of all the people

428
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:33,360
who refuse to believe in our current system.

429
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:34,800
With our government starting to collapse

430
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:35,760
with war imminent,

431
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:37,680
no one trusts our broken society.

432
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:39,200
And in the case of the Truman Show,

433
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,560
it's this unravelling madness

434
00:14:40,560 --> 00:14:42,000
that almost ends with Truman's wife

435
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,360
revealing her acted role.

436
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:45,520
Only until Truman's lifelong friend, Marlon,

437
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:46,640
bursts in at the last minute

438
00:14:46,640 --> 00:14:49,120
and whisks Truman away to have a heart-to-heart conversation.

439
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:49,840
But at this point,

440
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:52,000
it's like putting a bandaid on a gaping wound.

441
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,280
The floodgates are now open,

442
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:54,880
and Truman's belief is dwindling.

443
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:56,720
In this scene, the two are sitting near the river

444
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:57,760
and begin reminiscing.

445
00:14:57,760 --> 00:14:59,680
Christoph through Marlon reassures Truman

446
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:01,680
that Truman's life has meaning and is normal.

447
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:03,440
He comforts Truman by assuring him

448
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:05,120
that if what Truman believed was real,

449
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:07,760
then everyone would have to be in on it, including him.

450
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:10,560
Though this isn't possible as Marlon would never lie.

451
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:13,200
On the surface, Truman seemingly takes this into heart.

452
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,640
But deep down, he knows that Marlon

453
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:15,840
is just a victim of the game.

454
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:18,560
And so he deliberately shows to him that he bought the ruse.

455
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:20,400
He knows that Marlon isn't a bad person,

456
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,080
but that he's not a real person.

457
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:24,800
Morning arrives and Truman seems to be back to his old self.

458
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,560
He draws with a bar of soap on in the morning.

459
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:29,200
He has the usual conversations with his neighbours and co-workers,

460
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:32,160
and seems interested in a new office mate he will have next to him.

461
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:34,640
Evening rolls around and everything seems business as usual

462
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:35,920
with Truman fast asleep.

463
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:38,000
However, Christoph senses something is off.

464
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:41,040
Truman fell asleep in the basement rather than his bed.

465
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:43,360
So Marlon is again sent over with a six-pack

466
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:45,520
to investigate and talk Truman back to sense.

467
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:48,000
However, this time he finds that Truman isn't there

468
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,600
and has escaped from the house.

469
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:52,160
Christoph calls for all actors to search for Truman,

470
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:55,040
and for the first time in the show's history, cuts the transmission.

471
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:57,840
However, even with all the actors searching the entire set,

472
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:59,120
Truman cannot be found.

473
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:02,800
At his wit's end, Christoph has the set illuminated into daylight mode early.

474
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:05,680
And, on a hunch, has the team begin looking through the cameras

475
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:07,200
near the harbour and on the boat.

476
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:08,640
After cycling through a few cameras,

477
00:16:08,640 --> 00:16:10,560
the team finds Truman aboard a sailboat,

478
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:12,960
and Christoph gives the call to resume transmission.

479
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:14,560
After a few moments of peace sailing,

480
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:16,160
Christoph is then faced with a dilemma.

481
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:19,360
He either continues the transmission at risk of Truman finding the truth,

482
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:21,360
or he gets rid of Truman entirely.

483
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:24,320
So, he decides to send a violent storm above Truman's boat.

484
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:26,080
Christoph increases the violence of the weather,

485
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:28,160
but after a few long minutes, relents.

486
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:30,720
Amidst this, Truman shows his willingness to die for the truth.

487
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:31,840
By shouting to the sky,

488
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:33,040
is this the best you've got?

489
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:34,400
Christoph, in Godlike stupid,

490
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:36,960
descends to send the most violent bout of weather yet.

491
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:38,880
All to the dismay of his crew and producer.

492
00:16:38,880 --> 00:16:41,440
Truman, however, holds on, but is knocked unconscious.

493
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:44,480
But at the last minute, Christoph rescues the weather and removes the storm,

494
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:46,080
resuming the tranquil waters.

495
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:48,880
Truman regains consciousness and begins sailing his boat again.

496
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:51,520
He has beaten the storm and the sea seems to be in his favor.

497
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:52,800
However, after a few minutes,

498
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:55,440
the bow of Truman's boat launches through the side of the set,

499
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:57,040
leaving a big hole in the skydome.

500
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:59,600
By now, all of Truman's suspicions have been confirmed,

501
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:01,760
and in an ecstasy, begins punching the wall.

502
00:17:01,760 --> 00:17:04,640
However, the reality of Truman's situation begins to dawn on him,

503
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:06,560
as he sees the ramp at the end of the water.

504
00:17:06,560 --> 00:17:08,880
Truman walks across this ramp, walking on the water.

505
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:10,000
The audience is gripped.

506
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:13,840
The culmination of his 30 years in the Truman show seems to be at its finale.

507
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:17,200
Truman locates a staircase and slowly ascends to the side of the set.

508
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:20,080
At the top, he locates the door labeled exit and opens it,

509
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:21,600
revealing the abyss beyond his realm.

510
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:23,680
The gold-like voice then thunders through the sky,

511
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:28,000
as Christoph reveals that Truman was the star of the TV show with the whole world watching.

512
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,520
Truman asks, was nothing real?

513
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:32,240
And in response, Christoph responds that Truman is real,

514
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:34,560
and that's what made him so enjoyable for millions.

515
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:36,560
Christoph then tries to keep Truman in the set,

516
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:39,360
by indicating that there was no more truth out in the real world,

517
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:41,920
and that in the world he created for him, he had nothing to fear.

518
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:43,280
The ignorance was bliss.

